items.title: International Conference on Islamic Numismatics
items.body:
The Ministry of Culture is holding the International Conference on Islamic Numismatics, which emphasizes the significance of coins as an original document in the narrative of Islamic history. The conference is hosting the most prominent historians and directors of Islamic museums throughout the world, and long with the conference, there are scheduled workshops led by worldwide experts on coin restoration.

Book Now

 

Opening Hours: 

  • Day 1 is from 9:00 am to 4:00 pm
  • Day 2 from 2:00 PM to 6:30 PM
  • Day 3 from 10:00 am to 1:15 pm

items.title: Specialized Media conference
items.body: In the presence of His Excellency Dr. Badran Bin Abdulrahman Al-Omar, the president of King Saud University (KSU) in Riyadh, the Saudi Association for Media and Communication (SAMC) at King Saud University organizes Specialized Media conference. It includes specialized media, concepts and applications, political and military media, security and development media, health and environmental media, cultural and social media, administrative, economic and real estate media, sports, tourism and drama media.

items.title: Construction Event: The Big 5 Saudi
items.body: The Big 5 Saudi is connecting the construction industry in Saudi Arabia, co-located with HVAC R Expo Saudi, Stone & Surface Saudi Arabia, FM Expo Saudi, Windows, Doors & Facades and Saudi Glass, the event showcases products from the complete construction cycle in one place, at one time. Developed for the industry by listening to the industry, the Big 5 Saudi brings The Big 5 brand’s 40+ years’ experience and success to the Kingdom’s bustling construction and infrastructure projects market.

items.title: Green Riyadh: Afforestation of Al-Uraija Neighborhood
items.body:
Visit the event by "Green Riyadh" project and learn about the future vision of afforestation in Al-Uraija residential neighborhood. 

Green Riyadh program targets afforestation of more than 120 residential neighborhoods. The designs for afforestation work have been developed based on international standards that took into account the local environment. The project includes planting 7.5 million trees across the capital and it will contribute to an increase in per capita green space from 1.7 square meters to 28 square meters, and increase the total green space in the city to 9% or 545 square kilometers.

items.title: Shrek The Musical
items.body:
Shrek The Musical is based on the Oscar®-winning DreamWorks Animation film that started it all and is eagerly awaited by Riyadh's families and theatre enthusiasts, having already won not only many awards in various cities around the world but also the hearts of audiences everywhere. It is organized by the Royal Commission for Riyadh City and presented by DreamWorks Theatricals & Broadway Entertainment Group. This brilliant and fun-filled musical runs for 16 performances and is based on the all-star 2001 blockbuster Hollywood movie. Enjoy an amazing experience with your families, friends and loved ones.  Play will only be in English language.

Book Now

items.title: International Museum Day
items.body: Coinciding with International Museum Day on May 18, Saudi National Museum organizes bundle of Museum activities, from May 18 to 19, that a celebration of the International Museum Day, three cultural dialogue meetings and a workshop, all of which cover a range of topics, including “Museum as a Community Activator”, which will discuss the heritage preserved by museums, which reflects the progress of society, through humanities and art themes that take into account aspects of social and mental health, "Museum as an Inspiring Source", which will shed light on the role of the museum in enhancing the creative experience and its ability to inspire, as well as "The Arabian Peninsula as an Open Museum", which will review the beauty inherent in this land and its heritage, along with two workshops titled "The Past is an Extended Rope", targeting adults and youths, and reflecting on the relationship between the past and the present. These activities are part of the programmes organized by the National Museum targeting various segments of society through interactive activities, including: live performances, workshops, dialogue sessions, as well as activities related to national events with the aim of providing attractive cultural content and an integrated museum experience for its visitors. Visiting hours start from 8 to 10 pm on Thursday, and from 5 pm to 10 pm on Friday.

geofield.address: National Museum of Saudi Arabia, Riyadh

items.title: SFA Expo
items.body:
The SFA Expo is a 3-day event to discover established global and regional brands and services that are making waves in the sports, wellness, and fitness industries. This event brings together industry professionals, athletes, coaches, and fitness enthusiasts from around the world to share their knowledge and expertise. The SFA EXPO is the first of its kind "Sport For All EXPO" in the region, offering something for everyone to discover new ways to take care of their mind and body. SFA Expo offers the perfect opportunity to network with industry experts, establish grassroots connections, and tap into the growing Saudi market. From networking to learning, exploring to playing, and even competing, the Expo is your ultimate destination. It will also host the CSGs Awarding Ceremony to recognize the outstanding efforts of Community Sport Groups (CSGs).

Book Now
